    "Human responses on these DT tasks tend to follow a diminishing returns curve before reaching a plateau for an individual's more original responses 53.",
    "The higher levels of elaboration and semantic distance in AI responses suggests that the LLM processing possibly does not need this ramp-up time as seen in human responses, therefore LLM's can respond with their highest level of original responses when prompted.",
    "Whereas humans may fixate on more obvious responses at first, this algorithmic trait could then serve as an aid in overcoming ideation fixedness in humans.",
